<p><br clear="all" /></p>
<p><a name="Reception" id="Reception"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Vagrant_Story&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Reception">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Reception</span></h2>
<p>In May 2000, <i>Vagrant Story</i> became the fifth best-selling PlayStation title. 100,000 units were sold in the first 20 days of the game's release,<sup id="cite_ref-IGN_0-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-IGN-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> despite being overshadowed by other Square titles like <i><a href="/wiki/Final_Fantasy_IX" title="Final Fantasy IX">Final Fantasy IX</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/Chrono_Cross" title="Chrono Cross">Chrono Cross</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-IGN_0-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-IGN-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> <i>Vagrant Story</i> was the third of nine games to date, and the only game on the PlayStation, to receive a perfect score of 40 from <i><a href="/wiki/Famitsu" title="Famitsu">Famitsu</a></i> <a href="/wiki/Video_game_magazine" title="Video game magazine" class="mw-redirect">magazine</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-50" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-50" title=""><span>[</span>51<span>]</span></a></sup> The game has been called "the only outstanding title in the <a href="/wiki/Ivalice" title="Ivalice">Ivalice</a> mythology" by gaming website <a href="/wiki/1UP.com" title="1UP.com">1UP.com</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-kawazu_interview_46-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-kawazu_interview-46" title=""><span>[</span>47<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table class="collapsible" style="float: right; width: 23em; font-size: 80%; text-align: center; margin:0.5em 0 0.5em 1em;padding:0;background:transparent;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr>
<th style="font-size:120%;"><span style="padding-left: 2.25em;">&#160;</span>Reception</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<table class="infobox wikitable" style="width:100%;margin:0;border-bottom:none;" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0">
<tr>
